U.S. Congressman to Propose Rules for Muni Bonds, WSJ Reports

-- B y   G r e g   C h a n g
-- 
2011-04-13T19:14:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-13/u-s-congressman-to-propose-rules-for-muni-bonds-wsj-reports.html
U.S. Congressman Patrick McHenry, a
Republican from  North Carolina , plans to propose legislation to
make municipal-bond issuers subject to financial-disclosure
regulations set by the Securities and Exchange Commission, the
Wall Street Journal reported, citing the lawmaker.  The municipal-bond issuers would be required to comply with
Government Accounting Standards Board guidelines, McHenry told
the WSJ.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Greg Chang at 
 gchang1@bloomberg.net  